  "prompt": "Can pigs show affection?",
  "response": "Yes, pigs can show affection. They are highly intelligent and social animals, capable of forming strong bonds with humans and other animals. Pigs may demonstrate affection in various ways, such as nuzzling, licking, or following their caregivers around. They can also express excitement and happiness through playful behavior. Observations of pigs show that they can be quite sociable, enjoying interaction and companionship, which further indicates their capacity for affection.",
